comment: Forbes (SAS) makes contact to Napier's (POR) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Leonard (POR) makes contact to the body of Simmons (SAS) on the dunk.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of SAS possession is confirmed.
Layman (POR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Anderson (SAS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Simmons (SAS) makes marginal contact with Napier (POR) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Napier (POR) has part of his hand underneath the ball when he brings it to a pause and continues his dribble.
Dedmon (SAS) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Anderson (SAS) makes incidental contact with Connaughton (POR) that does not affect his SQBR.
Forbes (SAS) pushes off Napier (POR) and dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Napier (POR) makes marginal contact with Forbes (SAS) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Vonleh (POR) and Anderson (SAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Vonleh (POR) makes contact to Anderson (SAS) that affects his SQBR.
Dedmon (SAS) makes incidental contact with Connaughton (POR) that does not affect his SQBR.
Connaughton (POR) makes incidental contact with Simmons (SAS) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Leonard (POR) sets the screen on Simmons (SAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dedmon (SAS) makes incidental contact with Napier (POR) that does not affect his SQBR.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Vonleh (POR) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
